---
title: Italian Hoagie Salad with Prosciutto with Creamy Italian Dressing & Croutons
description: It’s always tasty in Philadelphia! Well, it is if you’re eating what they call a hoagie (aka. a sub, a hero, a grinder). But if you’re looking for a lighter salad option, have we got a great lunch idea for you! We take all the fillings—prosciutto, bell pepper, tomato, cucumber—and toss them with crisp lettuce, creamy Italian dressing, a sprinkle of oregano, and crushed croutons on top for crunch. That’s right: Philly is in the house.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/647f421302d358ae80bae44a-5316b84a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/647f421302d358ae80bae44a.pdf
time required: 10 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 410 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 23 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 900 mg
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-hoagie-salad-with-prosciutto-647f421302d358ae80bae44a
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop into bite-size pieces. Halve, core, and slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Slice @mini cucumber{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce}, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. Add lettuce, bell pepper, cucumber, and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; toss to coat.

> For 4 servings, use all the oregano, 2 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp sugar.

Tear @prosciutto{2%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Gently crush @croutons{1} in their bag.

> Refrigerate prosciutto until ready to use, so it's easier to tear!

Divide salad between bowls. Top with prosciutto and crushed croutons. Serve.